	<td>
	  <font size="2" face="Verdana">
		Subject:&nbsp;<b>post level 40 fighting tactics</b></font>
		
		<a href="MB_Editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=611309&TN=post+level+40+fighting+tactics&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=611309&PL=4&amp;action=REPLY"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/btn_reply.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Reply to message"></a>
		<br>
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/Icons/icon1.gif" border="0" align="ABSCENTER" width="15" height="15">
		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 1/2/2001 5:21:44 PM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=611309&TN=post+level+40+fighting+tactics&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=611309&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Perhaps it's because I'm fighting in the Dreadlands, but at level 43 I still find myself swinging two weapons during a fight, a lot.  I usually twist the level 36 Celerity song with the Curtailing Chant and Chant of Flame.  I figured that by this level I would be totally instrument driven, and doing great damage.  I've got pretty decent charm, but still find myself swinging away with the Yak, and being resisted fairly frequently.<BR>Possibly a problem with the groups I'm in, as there is usually only one true tank.<BR>Any tips or recommendations would be appreciated.  I'm still enjoying the game, and leveling at a decent rate, but thought I would have given my Yak away a long time ago.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
