	<td>
	  <font size="2" face="Verdana">
		Subject:&nbsp;<b>RE: post level 40 fighting tactics</b></font>
		
		<a href="MB_Editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=611309&TN=post+level+40+fighting+tactics&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=611477&PL=4&amp;action=REPLY"><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/btn_reply.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Reply to message"></a>
		<br>
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/Icons/icon1.gif" border="0" align="ABSCENTER" width="15" height="15">
		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 1/2/2001 7:57:50 PM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="US_Show.asp?id=12950">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/profile.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to See the Profile for Drineas Starsinger" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MSG_MailBox.asp?mode=new&amp;sendto=Drineas+Starsinger">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/privatemsg.gif" border="0" alt="Click Here to Message Drineas Starsinger" width="22" height="11"></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=60&FN=Bard&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=611309&TN=post+level+40+fighting+tactics&CAT=Classes&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=611477&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">Depends on the group I'm in as well as your actual level, but here's my suggestion in general.  There are some situations in which I still use different songs, but this is just a general lineup:</P><P>If only a single melee class, I hate saying this, but I generally stay on mana regen. =\  Keep the mana of the four casters up has generally been more efficient for me than doing damage, as far as total downtime and exp has gone.  This generally involves me not meleeing at all, since the casters aren't normally right in the thick of the fight.</P><P>If two melee'ers, but one or both is using 2HS weapons, I tend to go full damage using instruments.  Twist I use is Cantana of Soothing, Chords of Dissonance, Denon's Disruptive Discord, and Chant of Flame/Frost.  I tend to leave Fufil's out of that... Denon's and Chant of Flame/Frost do more damage than either Chords or Fufil's, where Fufil's and Chords do basically equal damage.  I go with Chords because it's resisted a lot less.</P><P>If three or four melee classes and a healer, and no enchanter/shaman, I go with, in this order, Largo's Melodic Binding, Celerity, Chant of Battle, Cantana of Soothing.  That minimizes the damage taken, maximizes the damage the melee'ers do, and keeps the casters in the group happy.  I keep the weapons in my hand for Largo's and Celerity, then switch to instruments for Chant of Battle and Cantana.</P><P>If three melee, enchanter, and healer, I go with, again in this order, Psalm of Cooling, Celerity, Chant of Battle, and Cantana.  Again, weapons for the first two songs, instruments for the second two.</P><P>If three or four melee and no healer or enchanter, I go with Largo's Melodic Binding, Celerity, Chant of Battle, and Hymn of Restoration.  I leave clarity for downtime, as healing as much as possible and avoiding damage is my main focus.  Again, weapons for first two, instruments for the second two.  This is also the twist I use if the groups is nothing but myself and melee classes, which actually happens quite a bit.  Five warriors/rangers/rogues and a bard really rips stuff apart.</P><P>Even with an enchanter in the group, I still keep Celerity up instead of Crescendo.  I prefer keeping the tanks from getting hit.  <shrug>  Others prefer Crescendo for the double attack/dual wield bonus.  That's up to you to decide on.</P><P>Honestly I don't frequently go full instrumental.  <shrug>  When I want to really rip into stuff myself I do, but... =\  One suggestion I do have, though.  Rather than getting weapons that do massive damage, focus on ones that have a high proc rate and have a useful proc.  Yaks are nice, but their proc calculation is rather low.  Harmonic daggers, gnollhide whips, anything that procs a time-stun instead of an instant stun is good.  Gnollhides proc a 3 second stun, harmonics proc a 5 second.  There's other out there, but I've found that those two weapons can help a bit.  If it's stunned, it's not hitting. <shrug>  Again, though, my fighting tactics differ greatly from most bards.  Not a matter of better, just a matter of style.</P><P>Also, the twist I suggest involve being able to twist four, as well as setting up hotkeys to allow two weapons, and two instruments, as well as four songs, and generally a fifth song hotkey for Pixie Strike/Song of Twilight for emergency mez.  Twisting four IS possible, but unless you're on a high-speed connection with a very good computer, you'll have a second's drop in each song before it refreshes.  That's worth it to me to get the added effects, even if they're not permanently up.</P><P>Drineas Starsinger<BR>Bard of the 53rd Song<BR>Luclin Realm<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
