		</font>
		<hr size="1">I also go back and forth.  My usual group is a druid, wizard, and myself.  If we are actually going hand to hand I usually keep my weapons on.  With my weapons and twisting in damage songs I can taunt the mob better (at least it seems to me).</P><P>If we are rooting/snaring and the like then I keep my tambourine in hand and twist flame chant/fufil's/frost chant.  I seldom try to twist 4 except in an emergency.  I always keep pixie strike, fear, and selos memmed (drop selos in a dungeon).  The druid keeps me sowed, but if we have to run I fire up selos and kill the sow.  Time it right and you don't slow down (no, I haven't had THAT much practise <G>).</P><P>For an all tank group I play all instrument- twisting in heal, celerity, and usually snare (unless a ranger is snaring).  I like the attack debuff on the snare.</P><P>In a mixed group I will usually go instrument and play what is appropriate.  If we are fighting casters I like the elemental rythms song for the resists.</P><P>I hardly ever play mana during combat.  The exception is when all the casters are running low and we may need that heal or nuke.</P><P>Hope this helps.</P><P>Kirico<BR>46 and out of hell<BR>Prexus<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
